Do not peel pineapple; wash thoroughly; core; cut the flesh and skin into chunks. Place into a large covered jar (like a pickle jar); add water, sugar, cloves, and cinnamon. Cap jar; store in warm place for 48 hours; uncap; stir. Add beer; allow tepache to continue to ferment for 24 hours more. Strain liquid; discard fruit; add sugar substitute. Chill. Serve cold over cracked ice.